The Mass Public Opinion Institute (MPOI), on Tuesday released results of their post-election survey, conducted last year. Titled Signs of Despair One Year after the GNU, the report reveals, among other things, that 47% of Zimbabweans think Mugabe is taking the country into the mountains .Below is a summry of issues covered in the 88-page document.Views on macro and micro-economic conditions Perceptions on the country s direction Incidence of deprivation/lived poverty Survival/livelihood strategies Views on government performance People s development agenda, awareness of state organs Views on accountability, trust in key institutions Perceptions of corruption, civic engagement Views on the new constitution People s views on the media and transitional justice Elections and election related issues Crime reporting and justice delivery Perceptions of opposition politics Perceived causes of Zimbabwe s economic problems Foreign/international assistance to Zimbabwe.